[
    {
        "text": "“Please raise\nyour right hand.”",
        "start": 0.11,
        "duration": 2.23
    },
    {
        "text": "These are the Supreme Court\nconfirmation hearings —",
        "start": 2.34,
        "duration": 2.515
    },
    {
        "text": "“This is day two.”",
        "start": 4.855,
        "duration": 1.145
    },
    {
        "text": "— you’re probably\nall familiar with.",
        "start": 6.0,
        "duration": 1.951
    },
    {
        "text": "“Bigly.”",
        "start": 7.951,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "“You just said ‘bigly.’”",
        "start": 8.45,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "“Bigly.”",
        "start": 9.53,
        "duration": 0.57
    },
    {
        "text": "Big partisan productions —",
        "start": 10.1,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "\"A charade and\na mockery.\"",
        "start": 11.282,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "“Anything else you want\nto say, Judge Bork?”",
        "start": 13.652,
        "duration": 2.118
    },
    {
        "text": "— that dominate the\nheadlines and the airwaves.",
        "start": 15.77,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "This is how they used to be.",
        "start": 18.41,
        "duration": 1.23
    },
    {
        "text": "[crickets]",
        "start": 19.64,
        "duration": 0.952
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, there actually\nweren’t any.",
        "start": 20.592,
        "duration": 1.778
    },
    {
        "text": "So how did we\nget from here —",
        "start": 22.37,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "[crickets]",
        "start": 23.75,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "— to here?",
        "start": 25.64,
        "duration": 0.84
    },
    {
        "text": "We’ll start in 1937 with\nformer Senator Hugo Black,",
        "start": 26.48,
        "duration": 3.81
    },
    {
        "text": "who’s being congratulated.",
        "start": 30.29,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "That’s because\nhe’s just been confirmed",
        "start": 32.15,
        "duration": 1.73
    },
    {
        "text": "as a Supreme Court Justice.",
        "start": 33.88,
        "duration": 1.81
    },
    {
        "text": "He’s also been outed\nas a former member",
        "start": 35.69,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "of the Ku Klux Klan.",
        "start": 37.62,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "So to explain himself,\nhe gets on the radio.",
        "start": 39.38,
        "duration": 2.55
    },
    {
        "text": "“I did join the Klan.",
        "start": 41.93,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "I later resigned.",
        "start": 44.12,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": "I never rejoined.”",
        "start": 46.79,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "People are not happy.",
        "start": 49.25,
        "duration": 1.699
    },
    {
        "text": "They’re basically asking:\nHow could the",
        "start": 50.949,
        "duration": 1.621
    },
    {
        "text": "Senate Judiciary Committee\nlet this guy through?",
        "start": 52.57,
        "duration": 2.59
    },
    {
        "text": "Answer:",
        "start": 55.16,
        "duration": 0.99
    },
    {
        "text": "Since the first hearing\nback in 1873, for this guy,",
        "start": 56.15,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "there were no standard\nways of holding hearings",
        "start": 59.51,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "for Supreme Court nominees.",
        "start": 61.49,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "They didn’t have\nto go and testify,",
        "start": 63.32,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "and the hearings didn’t\nneed to be made public.",
        "start": 65.06,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "The senators reviewed the\nnominees among themselves.",
        "start": 67.82,
        "duration": 3.24
    },
    {
        "text": "But then came a\ncouple of amendments",
        "start": 71.06,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "to the Constitution.",
        "start": 72.56,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "The upshot is they gave more\nvoting power to the people.",
        "start": 73.85,
        "duration": 2.82
    },
    {
        "text": "So the senators needed to\nstart paying more attention",
        "start": 76.67,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "to public opinion.",
        "start": 78.92,
        "duration": 1.176
    },
    {
        "text": "And they’re paying\nattention when",
        "start": 80.096,
        "duration": 1.374
    },
    {
        "text": "Black’s controversial\nconfirmation",
        "start": 81.47,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "drives Americans to ask: Why\nare these hearings private?",
        "start": 83.54,
        "duration": 4.314
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s a big reason why the\nnext nominee to come along",
        "start": 87.854,
        "duration": 2.166
    },
    {
        "text": "gets a public hearing.",
        "start": 90.02,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "And it’s not just\na public hearing,",
        "start": 91.82,
        "duration": 1.47
    },
    {
        "text": "it’s the first\nthat includes",
        "start": 93.29,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "no-holds-barred questioning\nby the committee.",
        "start": 95.3,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "Things are\nbeginning to change.",
        "start": 97.04,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "Then World War II\ncomes, and goes.",
        "start": 99.26,
        "duration": 4.9
    },
    {
        "text": "America is suddenly\na superpower.",
        "start": 104.16,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "Business booms,\nsuburbs grow.",
        "start": 106.12,
        "duration": 1.91
    },
    {
        "text": "“The protest took the\nform of a boycott.”",
        "start": 108.03,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "And we see the beginning of\nthe modern civil-rights era.",
        "start": 109.83,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "In 1954, the court rules\nto end racial segregation",
        "start": 112.63,
        "duration": 3.24
    },
    {
        "text": "in schools.",
        "start": 115.87,
        "duration": 1.587
    },
    {
        "text": "And this marks a\npoint where we really",
        "start": 117.457,
        "duration": 1.583
    },
    {
        "text": "start to see the court\nusing its power to shape",
        "start": 119.04,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "parts of American society.",
        "start": 121.32,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "That means Americans\ntake a greater interest",
        "start": 123.72,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "in who is on the court.",
        "start": 125.97,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "That means even more\npressure on senators",
        "start": 127.35,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "to vet these candidates.",
        "start": 129.69,
        "duration": 1.912
    },
    {
        "text": "Starting with the first nominee\nafter the Brown decision,",
        "start": 131.602,
        "duration": 2.878
    },
    {
        "text": "almost every nominee\nwill have a public hearing.",
        "start": 134.48,
        "duration": 4.03
    },
    {
        "text": "Now change is in full swing.",
        "start": 138.51,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "“I Have a Dream,” the\nmarch from Selma,",
        "start": 140.46,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "“The Feminine Mystique.”",
        "start": 142.71,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "The court keeps making\ncontroversial rulings",
        "start": 144.3,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "on race discrimination,\ngender discrimination,",
        "start": 146.76,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "personal privacy.",
        "start": 149.1,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "That means more\npublic interest,",
        "start": 150.48,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "more pressure on\nsenators, more issues",
        "start": 152.19,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "to parse in the hearings.",
        "start": 154.2,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "So the hearings get longer.",
        "start": 155.7,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "But just wait.",
        "start": 157.8,
        "duration": 1.298
    },
    {
        "text": "1981 — game changer.",
        "start": 161.35,
        "duration": 3.32
    },
    {
        "text": "“Good evening.",
        "start": 164.67,
        "duration": 0.85
    },
    {
        "text": "Sandra O’Connor —”",
        "start": 165.52,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "First woman nominated\nto the Supreme Court,",
        "start": 166.66,
        "duration": 2.18
    },
    {
        "text": "first nomination\nhearing to be televised.",
        "start": 168.84,
        "duration": 3.13
    },
    {
        "text": "The longer senators talk,\nthe more TV time they get.",
        "start": 171.97,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "The more TV time\nthey get, the more",
        "start": 175.63,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "they can posture for\nvoters watching at home.",
        "start": 177.25,
        "duration": 2.17
    },
    {
        "text": "[senators talking]",
        "start": 179.42,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "So the more they talk.",
        "start": 180.95,
        "duration": 1.459
    },
    {
        "text": "With the cameras rolling,\nwe’ll see",
        "start": 182.409,
        "duration": 1.701
    },
    {
        "text": "10 out of the 12\nlongest hearings ever.",
        "start": 184.11,
        "duration": 3.01
    },
    {
        "text": "One of those is\nfor Robert Bork —",
        "start": 187.12,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "“With a negative\nrecommendation",
        "start": 189.28,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "of 9 to 5.”",
        "start": 191.02,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "— who famously\ndoesn’t make the cut.",
        "start": 192.76,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "Now onto the aughts.",
        "start": 195.1,
        "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
        "text": "There’s an 11-year gap\nbetween nominees.",
        "start": 196.92,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Meanwhile, America has become\nmore politically divided,",
        "start": 199.24,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "so has the Senate.",
        "start": 202.15,
        "duration": 1.17
    },
    {
        "text": "“Over and over again —”",
        "start": 203.32,
        "duration": 0.465
    },
    {
        "text": "“Wait just a second —”",
        "start": 203.785,
        "duration": 0.795
    },
    {
        "text": "“How many times do we do\nthis before —”",
        "start": 204.58,
        "duration": 3.42
    },
    {
        "text": "Here’s Chief Justice Roberts\nto explain",
        "start": 208.0,
        "duration": 1.699
    },
    {
        "text": "what happened next.",
        "start": 209.699,
        "duration": 1.421
    },
    {
        "text": "“I mean, you look at two of\nmy colleagues, Justice Scalia",
        "start": 211.12,
        "duration": 3.45
    },
    {
        "text": "and Justice Ginsburg,\nfor example.",
        "start": 214.57,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "Maybe there were two or\nthree dissenting votes",
        "start": 216.94,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "between the two of them.”",
        "start": 219.54,
        "duration": 1.61
    },
    {
        "text": "Yep, three votes against\nGinsburg in 1993.",
        "start": 221.15,
        "duration": 3.08
    },
    {
        "text": "No votes against\nScalia in 1986.",
        "start": 224.23,
        "duration": 3.09
    },
    {
        "text": "“Now you look at my\nmore recent colleagues",
        "start": 227.32,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "and the votes were, I think,\nstrictly on party lines.”",
        "start": 229.39,
        "duration": 4.41
    },
    {
        "text": "That’s pretty much right.",
        "start": 233.8,
        "duration": 1.47
    },
    {
        "text": "“And that doesn’t\nmake any sense.”",
        "start": 235.27,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "And that’s how we got here.",
        "start": 237.34,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m not looking to take\nus back to quill pens.”",
        "start": 238.7,
        "duration": 3.59
    },
    {
        "text": "Very long —",
        "start": 242.29,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "“Nah, I just asked you where\nyou were at on Christmas.”",
        "start": 243.11,
        "duration": 2.47
    },
    {
        "text": "[laughter]",
        "start": 245.58,
        "duration": 0.685
    },
    {
        "text": "Always very political —",
        "start": 246.265,
        "duration": 1.125
    },
    {
        "text": "“So your failure to answer\nquestions is confounding me.”",
        "start": 247.39,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "— very public Supreme Court\nconfirmation hearings.",
        "start": 251.71,
        "duration": 3.97
    },
    {
        "text": "Also, something else to notice:\nSometimes these nominees",
        "start": 256.39,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "give pretty similar answers.",
        "start": 259.18,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "“The right to\nprivacy is protected",
        "start": 260.74,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "under the Constitution\nin various ways.”",
        "start": 262.87,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "“And it protects the right to\nprivacy in a number of ways.”",
        "start": 265.15,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "“In various places\nin the Constitution.”",
        "start": 267.85,
        "duration": 3.48
    },
    {
        "text": "“In a variety of places\nin the Constitution.”",
        "start": 271.33,
        "duration": 2.345
    },
    {
        "text": "“It’s protected by\nthe Fourth Amendment.”",
        "start": 273.675,
        "duration": 2.035
    },
    {
        "text": "“The Fourth Amendment\ncertainly speaks",
        "start": 275.71,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "to the right of privacy.”",
        "start": 277.87,
        "duration": 1.485
    },
    {
        "text": "“It’s founded in the\nFourth Amendment.”",
        "start": 279.355,
        "duration": 2.685
    },
    {
        "text": "“The first and\nmost obvious place",
        "start": 282.04,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "is the Fourth Amendment.”",
        "start": 283.81,
        "duration": 1.73
    }
]